Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 20:04:06 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Adapt retryablehttp callbacks to v0.7.8 API

The production changes only update unexported local callback literals assigned to retryablehttp.Client fields.

circonus-gometrics v1.2.0 source uses the old callback shape:

  CheckRetry(resp *http.Response, err error)

  RequestLogHook(logger *log.Logger, req *http.Request, retryNumber int)

The packaged go-retryablehttp v0.7.8 requires:

  CheckRetry(ctx context.Context, resp *http.Response, err error)

  RequestLogHook(logger retryablehttp.Logger, req *http.Request, retryNumber int)

This does not change circonus-gometrics exported API. The new context and logger parameters are unused, so retry decisions, last error handling, and retry-attempt accounting stay unchanged.

The remaining test changes avoid Go-version-sensitive exact stdlib error string checks and fix one malformed Fatalf call.
---
 api/api.go                 | 3 ++-
 api/api_test.go            | 4 ----
 checkmgr/checkmgr_test.go  | 2 +-
 circonus-gometrics_test.go | 4 ----
 submit.go                  | 5 +++--
 5 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/api/api.go b/api/api.go
index f3cd8cd..fa8b017 100644
--- a/api/api.go
+++ b/api/api.go
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@ package api
 
 import (
 	"bytes"
+	"context"
 	crand "crypto/rand"
 	"crypto/tls"
 	"crypto/x509"
@@ -280,7 +281,7 @@ func (a *API) apiCall(reqMethod string, reqPath string, data []byte) ([]byte, er
 
 	// keep last HTTP error in the event of retry failure
 	var lastHTTPError error
-	retryPolicy := func(resp *http.Response, err error) (bool, error) {
+	retryPolicy := func(ctx context.Context, resp *http.Response, err error) (bool, error) {
 		if err != nil {
 			lastHTTPError = err
 			return true, err
